From: robert-brunson-fragile <siinspam@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 12:05:56 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 05/13] feat(model): allow provider-scoped model picker
 allowlist

Add model_picker.allow so users can restrict picker visibility to exact provider/model pairs. The filter is provider-scoped, so gpt-5.5 can be shown only for openai-codex without also surfacing OpenAI API, Nous, or OpenRouter variants.

The policy is picker-only: explicit /model switches remain available for power users, while CLI/TUI/dashboard picker payloads share the filtered inventory centrally.

Co-authored-by: Nako <280596805+nakoagent@users.noreply.github.com>

